Analyzing only the petrol engines, what is the general relationship between engine volume (in cc) and acceleration performance (the 0-100km/h time)? Justify your answer with examples.
answer: There is a strong negative correlation between engine volume and the 0-100km/h time for petrol engines, meaning as engine volume increases, the time to accelerate to 100km/h generally decreases (performance improves). For example, the smallest petrol engine, the 1.4 16v (1390 cc), has the slowest time of 15.6 seconds. In contrast, the largest engine, the 2.8 24v (2792 cc), has the fastest time of 7.6 seconds. This trend is consistent across most of the range.
